  "local_port": 37318,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you reduce the magnification of your screen?",
  "response": "To reduce the magnification of your screen, you can adjust the zoom level or display settings depending on the device and operating system you're using. Here are the steps for common platforms:\n\n---\n\n### **On Windows:**\n1. **Using Keyboard Shortcuts:**\n   - Press `Ctrl` + `-` (minus key) to zoom out in most browsers and applications.\n\n2. **Change Display Settings:**\n   - Right-click on the desktop and select **Display settings**.\n   - Under **Scale and layout**, adjust the **Display resolution** or **Scale** to a lower percentage.\n\n3. **Magnifier Tool (if enabled):**\n   - Press `Windows` + `-` (minus key) to reduce magnification if the Magnifier is active.\n\n---\n\n### **On macOS:**\n1. **Using Keyboard Shortcuts:**\n   - Press `Cmd` + `-` (minus key) to zoom out in most browsers and applications.\n\n2. **Display Settings:**\n   - Go to **System Settings** > **Displays**.\n   - Adjust the **Resolution** or **Scale** to a lower setting.\n\n3. **Zoom Feature (if enabled):**\n   - Press `Option` + `Cmd` + `-` (minus key) to reduce magnification if Zoom is active.\n\n---\n\n### **On Web Browsers:**\n- Press `Ctrl` + `-` (Windows) or `Cmd` + `-` (Mac) to zoom out.\n- Alternatively, access the browser's settings menu (usually represented by three dots or lines) and adjust the zoom level.\n\n---\n\n### **On Mobile Devices:**\n1. **iOS (iPhone/iPad):**\n   - Double-tap with three fingers to reduce magnification if Zoom is enabled.\n   - Alternatively, go to **Settings** > **Accessibility** > **Zoom** and adjust or disable the feature.\n\n2. **Android:**\n   - Pinch two fingers together on the screen to zoom out.\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Accessibility** > **Magnification** to adjust or disable magnification.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you need help with a specific device or software!",
